  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Hungary and Poland: Training Workshop for the Promotion of Ethical Recruitment and Fair Labour Practices in Electronics Supply Chain</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IOM Corporate Responsibility in Eliminating Slavery and Trafficking (CREST) focuses on supporting companies and their suppliers to navigate new transparency and supply chain requirements, as well as supports them to adopt ethical recruitment principles and practices. Over the past few years, with consistent attention on electronics companies regarding labour issues in their supply chains, Samsung Electronics has announced the development of &#x201C;Samsung Migrant Worker Guidelines&#x201D; at the end of 2017. To extend its efforts to address forced labour in the supply chain, Samsung Electronics has requested IOM Republic of Korea (ROK) to provide CREST Training for the managers in Poland and Hungary factories and its suppliers in the countries. The project aims to enhance Samsung Electronics&#x2019; efforts to combat human trafficking and modern slavery in their supply chains.</narrative>
  </description>
